LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - EUROPE (19): ITALY, PREPAREDNESS, PREVENTION
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 29 Jul 2016
Source: Italian Ministry of Health press release [in Italian, machine trans., edited]
http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/news/p3_2_1_1_1.jsp?lingua=italiano&menu=notizie&p=dalministero&id=2651


The Ministry of Health draws attention to the risk of introduction into the national territory of the lumpy skin disease virus (lumpy skin disease) and has intensified the measures of prevention and surveillance.

Lumpy skin disease [LSD] is a viral disease that affects cattle, not transmissible to humans. In animals it causes fever, salivation, lacrimation, nasal discharge and typical skin lesions of nodular form from which it derives its name. In the affected farms, LSD is responsible for serious economic losses, resulting from the decrease in milk production, abortions and fertility disorders. Transmission between animals occurs through arthropod vectors, such as flies, mosquitoes and ticks, but direct infection or indirect by contaminated instruments is not excluded.

LSD is an exotic disease, subject to mandatory reporting.

The presence of the disease to date has been confirmed in Turkey, Greece, Bulgaria, the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia (FYROM), Serbia, Kosovo, Albania and Montenegro.

Italy is still unscathed, but the rapid spread of the disease in several countries of the Middle East and Eastern Europe has led to the blocking of the movement of animals from infected areas, and calls for an intensification of surveillance activities.

The Ministry of Health and the Customs Agency are working closely together to strengthen the border control activities on vehicles engaged in international transport of live animals, with a focus on procedures for cleaning, disinfecting and disinsectization.

See:
Circular of 29 Jul 2016 - Alert Lumpy Skin Disease (LSD) - information elements and surveillance activities
http://www.trovanorme.salute.gov.it/norme/renderNormsanPdf?anno=2016&codLeg=55541&parte=1%20&serie=null [in Italian]

